# Coding Rules

## 1. Single Responsibility Principle

Each function MUST do ONE thing only.

---

## 2. Naming

* Use clear, descriptive names
* Avoid abbreviations unless standard

Bad:

* doStuff()

Good:

* generate_withdraw_scenario()

---

## 3. No Magic Values

* Use constants or config
* Avoid hardcoded values

---

## 4. Pure Functions (Preferred)

* Functions should not have side effects unless necessary

---

## 5. Early Return

* Avoid deep nesting
* Use early return pattern

---

## 6. Testability

* Code must be easily testable
* Avoid tight coupling

---

## 7. Comments

* Explain WHY, not WHAT
* Avoid redundant comments

---

## 8. Consistency

* Follow same patterns across the project
* Do not invent new patterns per file
